              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- T – Thermocycler -->
          <div class="letter-card" data-letter-content="T">
            <div class="letter-header">
              <span class="letter-big">T</span>
              <div>
                <h3>Thermocycler</h3>
                <p>
                  PCR machines cycle through temperatures to denature, anneal,
                  and extend DNA, creating millions of copies for analysis.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="video-single">
              <video src="thermocycler-clip.mp4" autoplay loop muted playsinline></video>
              <p class="video-caption">
                Example: a thermocycler running a PCR program.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- E – Enzyme -->
          <div class="letter-card" data-letter-content="E">
            <div class="letter-header">
              <span class="letter-big">E</span>
              <div>
                <h3>Enzyme</h3>
                <p>
                  Enzymes act as catalysts in almost every biological process,
                  including cutting DNA, copying it, or modifying proteins.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="video-single">
              <video src="enzyme-clip.mp4" autoplay loop muted playsinline></video>
              <p class="video-caption">
